—dorsal view (UFMG 37923). ♂: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1209,1227,1004,1026]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D</emphasis>
—frontal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1394,1411,1004,1026]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E</emphasis>
— lateral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[286,301,1035,1057]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">F</emphasis>
—dorsal view (UFV Araponga, MG, Brasil, 16/04/1989, E.F.Morato; Parque Florestal da Serra do Brigadeiro, MG). Scale bar = 1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344990/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" targetBox="[151,1436,1137,1637]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1659,1711]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1659,1681]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">FIGURE 9.</emphasis>
Hind basitarsus of male of 
<taxonomicName box="[562,678,1659,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Thygater" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latitarsis">
<emphasis box="[562,678,1659,1681]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">T. latitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[692,710,1659,1681]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
—Holotype; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[844,861,1659,1681]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
—male from Rio de Janeiro: Itatiaia—15/03/2007, A.A. Azevedo (UFMG 37881) (the arrows indicate the apical half of the hind basitarsus wider in A, narrower in B).
